refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
arraycubrid_column_names resourcereq_identifier
The cubrid_column_names function is used to get the column names of the query result by using req_identifier.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


  Array of string which containing column names, when process is successful. 



  &false;, when process is unsuccessful.

  &reftitle.examples;

   cubrid_column_names example


<?php
$req = cubrid_execute ($con, "select * from person");
if ($req) {
   $coltypes = cubrid_column_types ($req);
   $colnames = cubrid_column_names ($req);
   while (list ($key, $coltype) = each ($coltypes))
      echo $coltype;
   while (list ($key, $colname) = each ($colnames))
      echo $colname;
   cubrid_close_request ($req);
}
?>
